content:
I usually don't write reviews but feel that since patch 1.5, I feel the need to write one. I want to express my dislike on the current CDPR's business model and end product.

CP2077 was announced in 2013, entered pre-production stage in 2014 and production in 2015 assuming after the Witcher 3. I believe there must have been a big change to the development in 2017 after you (rather supreme leader Adam Badowski) spontaneously decided to cast Keanu Reeves (I don't blame you, he's a likable individual) as quasi the main protagonist in the game to the detriment of the player. I don't play tabletop RPG's but the main point of those RPG's is to have the character of the player to be on the forefront ! Or other players at least if it is a squad-based RPG. Didn't Mr. Pondsmith tell you that?

What happens following the gameplay announcement in 2018 can be condensed in that sinking scene in the Titanic movie where the musicians keep on playing. You end up throwing away roughly 4 years of development just because Johnny F*cking Silverhand has to be a major plot point and cut down your time to 2 years to finish arranging the story around him.

Since 2018, you ditched the concept of "released when ready" in favour of over-hyping, over-selling your game, to the point that even in my workplace people were aware of it, which doesn't have many gamers to start with.

Your game released, I also was expecting a bit too much to be honest, but CP2077 was my first pre-order and even wanted to gift to a friend for Christmas. Fast-forward now and oh boy...

After over a year of continued support on the game, you're better off pulling the plug and sell the rights to a studio that has the management, budget and experience to actually develop that kind of game (Rockstar comes to mind). I should have been more careful after your announcement in 2018 that you can't deliver what you promised based solely on your success of Witcher 3, which was the only title CDPR had a major success with.

After Patch 1.5 I still have issues with CD: 

- Customize after character creation (basic feature present in almost any RPG/action/whatever game nowadays);
- Cars are more "driveable", yes but can't change their colours, body, etc. (feature present in titles over 20 years old btw);
- Minimap is still as bad as before;
- New apartments to buy (yay I guess? But new mechanics, weapons, major gigs would have been better imo);
- No communication whatsoever, either you over-mediatise your game, or you go full silent mode (?); you publish a roadmap and call it a day! That's not how you communicate with your customers if you're in damage control mode!
- New story elements would have been cool, though you added some gigs;
- Pacifica... Well, Pacifica is Pacifica. Still boring, unpopulated and has lower crime-rates than a max security prison on riot without guards. Which is supposed to be the toughest neighbourhood in Night City; 
- Where are the new gangs you promised as well? (The clown ones and psycho ones?);
- No combat Arena;
- No transit features either - Modders have done it already;
- Badlands are as empty as my babushka's vodka bottle! (I believe Mitch or Scorpion state that the Badlands are actually full of dangers. We don't have the same notion of "full" I guess). Yes there are gigs and NCPD hustles here and there but there is no armed convoy from Militech, or hostile nomads, any sort of other activity...
- No repeatable, radiant missions (gang shootouts, corpo assassination, etc.). Some like, some dislike them but I think it's a nice feature that could have been inside to get us to try different builds, because once you reach lvl. 50, you're more powerful than Chuck Norris, Jesus and Santa Claus combined, and at that point, you beat the game! Yes there are NCPD alerts but it is preset in defined places and pop-up occasionally only, so you have to actively go hunt them because NCPD doesn't have the coordinates of the different crimes unless you drive by them;
- No New Game+;
- Some bugs are still present (car rains down on road or is catapulted over the Pacific) but they are rather funny to me, and I'm on PC so I can't complain on that because my config is rather top-tier and the game is surprisingly stable for me.
- Some perks got overhauled but as stated before, no concrete way to farm them or some are still not fixed (athletics, looking at you);
- Minor complaint : no new clothes, no cyberware visual overlays, transmog, etc.;
- 2 weapons added lately but still a low amount of choice. Status effects are locked to the weapon designer too, but I guess this can make sense lore-wise;

By trying to please everyone (Stadia, PS5, etc.) you end up pleasing no one. Design your products around fewer customer-bases and hardwares, then expand on it. You can expand on a success you developped for a niche, what baffles me is that the management in CDPR didn't take lessons from the Witcher 3's success (which is not my type of game) making the execs look like baboons squandering Polish government's and CDPR's investors' money away on "gambling" projects. CP2077 feels really like you gambled on making a big success and you chewed on more than you can bite.

I may seem being too hard on them but the game was sold for nearly 70 USD in my country, and features that are considered as basic in most games took nearly one year to implement. So of course I'm not going to be pleased that easily, consumers should remember that they vote with their wallet!

This review is long enough as it is already, and just want to add that I feel bad for the employees that sacrificed and crunched in order to meet hallucinatory expectations from management and PR dept.

EDIT: I still enjoy the game as underwhelming as it is but for anyone out there, decide carefully on what you want to buy from CDPR. I know I wouldn't put my trust in them again unless there is a big change in the management. They seem to turn the ship in the right direction but is still very late and trust takes time to build.
